description:
The Power of Representation
Sunday, February 15, 2015
Monica Kurzel-Runtscheiner
The Agnes Lynch Anderson and Roger Anderson Lecture
"The Hapsburgs: Rarely Seen masterpieces from Europe's Greatest Dynasty" is a sweeping exhibition showcasing the remarkable history of the Austrian Habsburg Emperors. Get the insights from the curator herself about the family who, over a span of 500 years, commissioned and collected households full of masterpieces by which to display their power. Monica Kurzel-Runtscheiner, PhD, is director of the Imperial Carriage Museum, Vienna, and curator of the exhibition.

title: Monica Kurzel-Runtscheiner - The Power of Representation
